Description:
    Creates an API controller for a model in the Api::V1 namespace, following the project's conventions.
    When the model is namespaced (e.g. Crm::Client), the controller is placed under api/v1/<module>/
    and all model constants use the root prefix (::Crm::Client) to avoid constant lookup issues.

Examples:
    # 无命名空间，生成 app/controllers/api/v1/clients_controller.rb
    rails g api:v1:scaffold_controller Client

    # 有命名空间，生成 app/controllers/api/v1/crm/clients_controller.rb，并自动创建 crm 目录
    rails g api:v1:scaffold_controller Crm::Client

    # 带属性
    rails g api:v1:scaffold_controller Crm::Client --attributes=code,name,parent_id,status

Options:
    --attributes=code,name,...   Comma-separated list of permitted attributes
    --skip-template-engine       Skip generating view templates
    --skip-assets                Skip generating assets
    --skip-helper                Skip generating helper
    --skip-resources             Skip generating resource
    --skip-routes                Skip generating routes
    --skip-test                  Skip generating test files

Note:
    - Controllers inherit from Api::V1::BaseController (or BaseController when namespaced).
    - For namespaced models (e.g. Crm::Client), the generator creates the module directory
      under app/controllers/api/v1/ if it does not exist and uses ::Module::Model in
      the generated code so that constant resolution works correctly under Api::V1.
